# u-forge.ai Project Structure Guide

Local-first TTRPG worldbuilding tool with AI-powered knowledge graphs. Built in Rust.

**Status:** Early prototype. CLI demo only. Migrating to Lemonade Server + SQLite + web UI.

## Architecture Overview

Read [ARCHITECTURE.md](mdc:ARCHITECTURE.md) for full details (module map, data model, known bugs, design decisions).
Read [migration.md](mdc:migration.md) for the phased migration plan.

## Current Architecture

- **Facade**: [src/lib.rs](mdc:src/lib.rs) — `KnowledgeGraph` struct (owns storage, embeddings, schemas) + `ObjectBuilder`
- **Storage**: [src/storage.rs](mdc:src/storage.rs) — RocksDB with 5 column families (nodes, edges, chunks, names, schemas)
- **Embeddings**: [src/embeddings.rs](mdc:src/embeddings.rs) — `EmbeddingProvider` trait + `FastEmbedProvider` (being replaced by `LemonadeProvider`)
- **Vector Search**: [src/vector_search.rs](mdc:src/vector_search.rs) — HNSW + FST hybrid (being replaced by sqlite-vec + FTS5)
- **Schemas**: [src/schema.rs](mdc:src/schema.rs) + [src/schema_manager.rs](mdc:src/schema_manager.rs) + [src/schema_ingestion.rs](mdc:src/schema_ingestion.rs)
- **Data Import**: [src/data_ingestion.rs](mdc:src/data_ingestion.rs) — JSONL two-pass import
- **Embedding Queue**: [src/embedding_queue.rs](mdc:src/embedding_queue.rs) — async background worker (not yet integrated)

## Migration Direction

Standardizing on **[Lemonade Server](https://github.com/lemonade-sdk/lemonade)** (AMD, OpenAI-compatible API) for all AI:
- Embeddings: `POST /api/v1/embeddings` replaces FastEmbed
- Reranking: `POST /api/v1/reranking` (new capability)
- Chat: `POST /api/v1/chat/completions` (future)

Storage migrating from RocksDB → **SQLite + FTS5 + sqlite-vec**.
UI via **axum** HTTP/WebSocket server.

## Key Integration Point

The `EmbeddingProvider` trait in [src/embeddings.rs](mdc:src/embeddings.rs) is the primary abstraction for AI capabilities. New providers (Lemonade, etc.) implement this trait. Do NOT bypass it.

## Known Bugs (see ARCHITECTURE.md for details)

- BUG-1: HNSW persistence broken (always rebuilds on startup)
- BUG-2: `similarity = 1.0 - distance` wrong for L2 (can go negative)
- BUG-3: Node deletion is O(N) across entire edge column family
- BUG-4: `get_stats()` is O(N) full table scan
- BUG-5: `Mutex<TextEmbedding>` blocks Tokio thread
- BUG-6: No import deduplication
- BUG-7: In-memory-only edge resolution during import

